.SH NAME
PSFONTS\(em\*(PS language font information for \*(TS programs
.SH DESCRIPTION
The following information lists the fonts which are supported in the
standard \*(TS release.  Additional fonts can be added to this list; see
the \*(TS installation guide for more details.
The fonts are available by full name when using the
enscript(1)
program,
and by short name when using
psroff(1)
or
[di]troff.
The font family refers to the name of the family that the particular
font belongs to.
It is used to declare a default set of fonts in
psroff(1),
ptroff(1),
etc.
.sp
A number of font families below use the same two characters to specify
all four font faces in the family.
The alphabetic case is varied to specify an individual face.
For example:
.br
Roman: xx,\ \ \ Bold: xX,\ \ \ Italic: Xx,\ \ \ Bold-Italic: XX.
.sp
Please note that alphabetic case is important in all three columns below. 
.sp
